						<h3>Ointment for pain in the knees and varicose veins</h3>
						<figure>
							<img src="./img/image00030.jpg" alt="">
						</figure>
						 <strong>Ointment for pain in the knees and varicose veins</strong><figure><div><div></div><div><img></div><div></div></div><meta><figcaption><span></span></figcaption></figure><p><span>Friends to all Hello, today I want to write about a ointment that can be made at home. </span></p><p><span>I myself suffered from such ailments as knee pain and varicose veins. This tool was recommended to me by a friend from Italians.</span></p><p><span><u><i>And here's what it takes:</i></u></span></p><p><span><b>Cedar gum or pine gum</b></span><span> - 100 grams</span></p><figure><div><div></div><div><img></div><div></div></div><meta><figcaption><span>Cedar gum </span></figcaption></figure><p><span><b>Beeswax </b></span><span>- 100 grams</span></p><figure><div><div></div><div><img></div><div></div></div><meta><figcaption><span>Beeswax</span></figcaption></figure><p><span><b>Any vegetable oil</b></span><span> - 200 grams</span></p><p><span><b>Propolis tincture</b></span><span> - 50 grams</span></p><figure><div><div></div><div><img></div><div></div></div><meta><figcaption><span>Propolis tincture</span></figcaption></figure><p><span><b>Bee ognevki extract</b></span><span>-50 drops</span></p><figure><div><div></div><div><img></div><div></div></div><meta><figcaption><span>Bee moth</span></figcaption></figure><blockquote><span>Friends, I want to warn you that such components as </span><span><b>cedar SAP</b></span><span> and </span><span><b>beeswax</b></span><span> were sent to me by a friend from Italy. Although, she in turn ordered them from</span><span><u><i>amazon</i></u></span><span>. This is an online store, something like </span><span><u><i>aliexpress.</i></u></span><span> I think that you can do all this on aliexpress prescribe.</span></blockquote><blockquote><span></span></blockquote><blockquote><span>Beeswax is also sold in Russia, in the markets, with small tiles.</span></blockquote><h3><span>We make an ointment:</span></h3><p><span>I take a plastic container, which by the way weighs 34 grams, and put 100 grams of cedar SAP in it.</span></p><figure><div><div></div><div><img></div><div></div></div><meta><figcaption><span>Cedar gum 100 grams. Don't forget to factor in the weight of the container</span></figcaption></figure><p><span><b>The same weighing process </b></span><span>is done with beeswax.</span></p><figure><div><div></div><div><img></div><div></div></div><meta><figcaption><span>Beeswax-100 grams.</span></figcaption></figure><p><span>If you have beeswax tiles, then grate it on a grater.</span></p><p><span>Next to the container add 200 grams of vegetable oil. Personally, I use corn oil.</span></p><figure><div><div></div><div><img></div><div></div></div><meta><figcaption><span>Vegetable oil-200 grams.</span></figcaption></figure><p><span></span></p><p><span><b>Now</b></span><span>I will prepare the ointment in a water bath. I take the pot, put a napkin on the bottom, later pour water into the pot and put it there container.</span></p><figure><div><div></div><div><img></div><div></div></div><meta><figcaption><span>The so-called water bath.</span></figcaption></figure><p><span>All that we weighed pour into an iron container. And put it on the stove, on a slow fire. The main thing is not to bring to a boil. Cook and stir for an hour.</span></p><figure><div><div></div><div><img></div><div></div></div><meta><figcaption><span>On low heat for an hour</span></figcaption></figure><p><span>Closer to the end of cooking, you will see that the wax has completely dissolved. But if the pieces of resin float, then cook further.</span></p><p><span>Friends, all the components of this ointment help our veins and vessels very much. </span></p><p><span><b>Cedar</b></span><span> gum increases blood circulation in the blood vessels, relieves inflammation. Increases blood flow, helps to eliminate blood clots.</span></p><p><span> </span><span><b></b></span><span>Beeswax has a regenerating and hemostatic effect.</span></p><p><span><b>Propolis</b></span><span> relieves swelling and pain, has a strong tonic effect and participates in the resorption of blood clots.</span></p><p><span> This medicine can be used smear not only on the legs and veins, but also eczema or some kind of dermatitis on the hands.</span></p><p><span></span></p><p><span><b>I have the ointment ready.</b></span><span> I do not filter it, because my broth is pure. If you have succeeded, with impurities, then you need to strain through cheesecloth.</span></p><figure><div><div></div><div><img></div><div></div></div><meta><figcaption><span>My broth without impurities'.</span></figcaption></figure><p><span> I wait for it to cool down and add propolis ( 50 grams) and bee sting ( 50 drops), mix thoroughly.</span></p><figure class="article-image article-image_lazy article-image_lazy-shown article-image_with-border-radius article-render__block article-render__block_image"><div><div class="article-image__placeholder article-image__placeholder_hidden"></div><div> "&gt;</div><div></div></div><meta><figcaption><span>It turns out such an ointment.</span></figcaption></figure><p><span></span></p><p><span> The composition of such an ointment is stored </span><span><b>for two years</b></span><span> in the refrigerator. </span></p><p><span>I'll show you how to apply it to the sore spots. </span></p><p><span>Most importantly, always approach treatment with common sense.</span></p><p><span>Thank you all, send it comments.</span></p><h3><span>Photo source: Yandex images.</span></h3><h2><span>Subscribe to the channel</span><span><u><i>Go to the OSS</i></u></span></h2><p><span></span></p><div></div>
